  "prompt": "What is the difference between Karunanidhi and Jayalalitha?",
  "response": "Karunanidhi and Jayalalitha were two prominent political leaders from Tamil Nadu, India, who were long-time political rivals. Here are some key differences:\n\n1. Political Party:\n- Karunanidhi: DMK (Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam) party leader\n- Jayalalitha: AIADMK (All India Anna Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam) party leader\n\n2. Political Philosophy:\n- Karunanidhi: More aligned with Dravidian ideology and social justice\n- Jayalalitha: Continued MGR's political legacy with a populist approach\n\n3. Leadership Style:\n- Karunanidhi: Known for being a skilled politician and writer\n- Jayalalitha: More authoritative and assertive leadership\n\n4. Background:\n- Karunanidhi: Screenwriter and journalist before entering politics\n- Jayalalitha: Film actress who transitioned into politics\n\n5. Tenure:\n- Karunanidhi: Multiple terms as Tamil Nadu Chief Minister\n- Jayalalitha: Multiple terms as Tamil Nadu Chief Minister\n\nBoth were influential leaders in Tamil Nadu politics, representing different ideological streams within the Dravidian movement, and their rivalry was a significant aspect of state politics for decades.",
